This paper deals with active learning from demonstration for robots, which involves machine learning, robotics, and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a risk-aware active inverse reinforcement learning algorithm, which involves optimization and control theory, making it likely to fall under the categories of cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.SY. The algorithm also utilizes performance bounds for inverse reinforcement learning, which involves statistical learning theory, making cs.LG a likely category as well. Finally, the experiments involve simulated driving and table setting tasks, which may involve computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV a possible category.
